Two people have died and at least 160 lost their homes when a fire broke out  in Cape Town on Saturday. The City’s Fire and Rescue Service spokesperson Theo Layne said a fire broke out in Pholeli Park and about 60 shacks were destroyed. “A community leader reported that 100 people were displaced while a 10-year-old boy died.” He added that 15 more shacks were destroyed in Symphony Way, leaving 60 people homeless. Meanwhile, a woman was reported dead in a house fire in Altena Road, Strand. The cause of the fire is undetermined but the police are still investigating. -TNA Reporter 